{"questionId":"27830","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Roy is a member of a motorsport club and regularly drives around the Port Campbell racetrack.</p>\n<p>The times he takes to complete a lap are normally distributed with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>59</mn></math> seconds and&nbsp;standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> seconds.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Roy will complete a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math> lap race. It is expected that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math> of the laps will take more than&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>correct use of expected value</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>p</mi></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>43</mn></math>&nbsp;seen&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>correct probability statement</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>43</mn></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp;indicated on sketch to communicate correct area&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/0a82c83495cea724790fbd2f4f9fa8efc08db2b6.png\"></p>\n<p><strong><br>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>59</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mtext>seconds</mtext></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>59</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5291</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27830","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.8b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of t.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}